</style><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1"><title>Mega Evolution | Pokemon Symbols</title><meta name="description" content="The Mega Evolution expansion for the Pokémon TCG reintroduces Mega Evolution Pokémon EX cards, marked by a black-and-yellow EX symbol, which are worth three prize cards when defeated. It includes over 180 cards, sourced mainly from Japan’s Mega Brave and Mega Symphonia sets, plus reprinted Trainers. This set debuts full-art ultra rare Item, Tool, and Stadium cards, revives Mirror Holofoil variants, and features 10 Mega Evolution Pokémon ex, 22 illustration rares, and 10 special illustration rares."><meta property="og:title" content="Mega Evolution | Pokemon Symbols"><meta property="og:description" content="The Mega Evolution expansion for the Pokémon TCG reintroduces Mega Evolution Pokémon EX cards, marked by a black-and-yellow EX symbol, which are worth three prize cards when defeated. It includes over 180 cards, sourced mainly from Japan’s Mega Brave and Mega Symphonia sets, plus reprinted Trainers. This set debuts full-art ultra rare Item, Tool, and Stadium cards, revives Mirror Holofoil variants, and features 10 Mega Evolution Pokémon ex, 22 illustration rares, and 10 special illustration rares."><meta property="og:image" content="https://pokesymbols.com/images/tcg/sets/symbols/mega-evolution.png"><meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image"><meta name="twitter:title" content="Mega Evolution | Pokemon Symbols"><meta name="twitter:description" content="The Mega Evolution expansion for the Pokémon TCG reintroduces Mega Evolution Pokémon EX cards, marked by a black-and-yellow EX symbol, which are worth three prize cards when defeated. It includes over 180 cards, sourced mainly from Japan’s Mega Brave and Mega Symphonia sets, plus reprinted Trainers. This set debuts full-art ultra rare Item, Tool, and Stadium cards, revives Mirror Holofoil variants, and features 10 Mega Evolution Pokémon ex, 22 illust